name: Back in the Jay...the art of Jason Reeves & 133art Vol.1
description:
It's finally here! 

The 'Back in the Jay' sketchbook is a collection of illustrations, conceptual designs, comic art, and some never-before-seen work, put together with the love & skill you've come to know from Studio 133art! 

25 pages Full color 

9 x 7in. / Prestige Hardcover

name: OneNation: Old Druids[Print Comic]
description:
133art presents: Onenation: Old druids 

Cover by: Lee Moyer
Written by: Alverne Ball 
Art by: Ari Syahrazad
................................................................................................
On a rainy night in London, what begins as two strangers sharing a drink in a pub becomes a night of dark occurrences. As a young Sundiata learns the cryptic secret of the Old Druids. Before Paragon, before the formation of the Tenth Foundation, he was just an ex-soldier looking for a new mission. The genesis of the mysterious Sundiata begins here!

Print version   24pgs. Black & White
**MATURE READERS**

name: OneNation#1 [print comic]
description:
ONENATION is a five-issue limited series featuring the hero Paragon, the first superhuman the world has ever seen, whose idealistic views of being a superhero and doing good for mankind is challenged when the reality of changing the world hits. At first harkening in name, design and deed to the likes of Captain America or Superman, as the series progresses Paragon; along with a rising generation of superhumans called Keramats, find the trappings of being a superhero ill-fitting when it comes to his larger role of saving the world...from itself.

30pgs. Full color   **MATURE READERS**
